<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title></title></head><body><div><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written Evidence Submitted by Keep Wales Tidy</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (KWT</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Background</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT is an independent National Voluntary Organisation with Charitable Status.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> We are </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">one of Wales’ largest and most effective environmen</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">tal charities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">covering the whole</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of Wales </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and influencing a wide range of organisations and communities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. Our approach leads to sustainable change</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">through </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">influencing behaviour and enabling individuals, groups and schools to take their own actions. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Our focus is on people </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and their connections with the environment. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We deal with far more than litter</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">our work encompasses biodiversity, access and recreation, health improvement, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">food growing, beach awards, Eco-</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Schools, Young Reporter for the Environment and so forth. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Our work is underpinned by research and policy work </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">including; Local Environmental Quality Surveys and developing advice for Government and other stakeholders.</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.51pt; padding-left:0.69pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">S</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ummary</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:4.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We support</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">introduction of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">single-use carrier bag </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(SUCB) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">charge in Wales. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> The S</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">U</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">CB charge</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> has successfully reduced the consumption of bags in Wales, which </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the environment</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> while the proceeds </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> benefit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> charitable causes, including environmental projects.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:4.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT‘s research </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has identified </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a marginal decrease in bag litter, but we recognise that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">our </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">data is likely to significantly understate the extent of littered carrier bags, since they are so easily transported by weather.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:4.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">would </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">like</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to see data on usage and street cleanliness continuously monitored. It may be beneficial to publicise the good causes that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT generates </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">from the proceeds of the charge</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, including amongst retailers</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:4.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">If</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> people </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">get used to paying for bags</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">it may lead</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> rise in</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> bag use </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in the future and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">consideration should be given to increasing the value of the charge. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">believe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a cost of up to 15p would be reasonable. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:4.14pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT agrees with the principles of the voluntary agreement and would like to see the whereabouts of the proceeds continuously monitored and publicised. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 13.51pt; padding-left:0.69pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Our Evidence</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In relation to the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">forthcoming charge for plastic bags in England</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, KWT would like to put forward the following evidence</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> based on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">our experience in relation to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">SUCB </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">levy in Wales.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT continues to support the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">SUCB </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">levy on the grounds that it both protects and improves our environment. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">It has successfully reduced the consumption of carrier bags in Wales, and therefore the impact they have in manufacture and disposal (including litter). Meanwhile the proceeds of the levy are making a tangible difference </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> many charitable causes, including environmental projects.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">SUCB l</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">evy came into being in Wales on 1</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> October 2011. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> was fully supportive of the Welsh Government in introducing the levy and the evidence below sets out our reasons for continued support</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> as well as suggestions moving forward. KWT understands that the W</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">elsh Government</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is to review the policy in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">November 2014</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, at which point KWT </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">will s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ubmit </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">further evidence</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In terms of u</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">sage</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.1bn single-use carrier bags were used in the UK in 2012; a 1.3% rise on th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">previous year. However, regional differences show that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Wales</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> carrier bag use fell over this </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">period by 76%</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In the same time frame, the number of bags used per person per month in Wales reduced from 7.4 to 1.8.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> W</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">elsh Government</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> information based on 13 </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">retailers</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> shows further reductions in carrier bag use of between 35-96%</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">after the introduction of the levy</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. This range suggests that some retail sectors</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">particularly food service and fashion</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> are harder to tackle than others </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">- </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and that targeted work may be needed for further improvements.   </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In measuring the success of the scheme, the Welsh Government has commissioned research to understand the extent of the reduction in bag use generated</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and to understand how the general public feels about the levy.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The levy has been </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">seen to increase own bag use in Wales from 61% </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to 82%</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Over this period public support for the levy has also increased</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> from 59% to 80%</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">K</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">WT</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> has observed a decrease in littered carrier bags through </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">our Local Environmental Audit and Management System </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">LEAMS</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">street</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> data, albeit only marginal. In the full survey year prior to the introduction of the levy carrier bags were found on an average of 1.1% of each local authority’s streets. Since the introduction of the levy that figure has dropped to 0.9%. The percentage of streets littered with carrier bags has reduced in 12 of the 22 local authorities and remained the same in a further four.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Meanwhile </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> has long recognised that street-data is likely to significantly understate the extent of littered carrier bags. This owes to the physical properties of carrier bags which render them not readily degradable, meaning they persist for long periods in the environment and are easily transportable by weathe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">r, causing wide dispersal. Keep Wales Tidy </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">staff and volunteers routinely remove bags that have blown in</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to trees and along river banks.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Proceeds from the Charge</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Waste (Wales) Measure 2010 gives Welsh Ministers the power create regulations which would impose duties on retailers on the destination of proceeds from the charge. However this has not been used; instead the W</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">elsh </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">overnment</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> advocates a voluntary agreement</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and the success of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">this agreement is to be measured by meeting the principles that:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The net proceeds are passed on to good causes.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-14.15pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Where possible, the net proceeds will benefit Wales.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The small number of businesses across Wales found to be failing to enforce the charge has been seen as a marker of the scheme’s success</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. The proceeds from the charge are making a substantial difference in Wales, with 100s of thousands of pounds already being pledged to ‘good causes’</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Going Forward</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT should like to see data on usage and street cleanliness continuously monitored. If support for the levy waivers, then it may be necessary to reinforce the messages which have, so far, succeeded in gaining support. It may also be beneficial to publicise the good causes that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">benefit </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">from the proceeds of the charge</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, including amongst retailers</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">E</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">xperience from the Republic of Ireland suggests that as time goes on, people may get used to paying for bags and, as such, bag use may rise. Should this prove to be the case then consideration should be given to increasing the value of the charge. KWT has previously stated that a cost of up to 15p would be reasonable. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 13.51pt; padding-left:0.69pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Bags for Life</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In addition, we’d like to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> include </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">inform</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ation on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the current debate in Wales relating to bags for life</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> linked to the proposed Environment Bill.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The ‘Towards the Sustainable Management of Wales’ Natural Resources’ White Paper </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">proposes to extend the enabling powers of the Welsh Ministers so that they may, by regulations, provide for minimum charges to be set for other types of carrier bags in addition to single use carrier bags</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">KWT agrees with this proposal due to the increased use and disposal of, for example bags for life, and the detrimental effect that these can have on the environment.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">However, we recognise the aims of the levy will have failed if the charge and distribution of funding goes on forever, as the key aim is change behaviour - reduce waste and litter and the negative environmental impacts.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.wrap.org.uk/content/wrap-publishes-new-figures-carrier-bag-use"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.wrap.org.uk/content/wrap-publishes-new-figures-carrier-bag-use</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.wrap.org.uk/content/wrap-publishes-new-figures-carrier-bag-use"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.wrap.org.uk/content/wrap-publishes-new-figures-carrier-bag-use</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><a href="http://wales.gov.uk/topics/environmentcountryside/epq/waste_recycling/substance/carrierbags/reduction/?lang=en"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://wales.gov.uk/topics/environmentcountryside/epq/waste_recycling/substance/carrierbags/reduction/?lang=en</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><a href="http://wales.gov.uk/topics/environmentcountryside/epq/waste_recycling/substance/carrierbags/attituderesearch/?lang=en"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://wales.gov.uk/topics/environmentcountryside/epq/waste_recycling/substance/carrierbags/attituderesearch/?lang=en</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.carrierbagchargewales.gov.uk/retailers/reportingback/?lang=en"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.carrierbagchargewales.gov.uk/retailers/reportingback/?lang=en</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Only six businesses found in breach of the carrier bag charge’, The Western Mail, 10/09/12</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">‘Carrier bag charge reduces bag handout by up to 96%’, The Western Mail, 18/07/12</span></p></body></html>